    "body": "  ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                                 \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\nEnables `MoEActivation.GELU` (gated GELU, GeGLU) on the FlashInfer TRT-LLM NvFP4 MoE backend (`TrtLlmNvFp4Experts*` in  `vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/experts/trtllm_nvfp4_moe.py`). The  GPU kernel and the dispatcher already support GeGLU end-to-end — only the Python allow-list and assertions were gating it out.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \r\n\r\nThis is also the first kernel-level test for the TRT-LLM × NvFP4 intersection in vLLM — sibling backends (CUTLASS NvFP4 in test_flashinfer_moe.py) and sibling quants (TRT-LLM FP8 in test_flashinfer.py) had tests, but the specific kernel and quant scheme this PR enables had no coverage. \r\nThe swizzle-flag fix in make_test_quant_config was a latent test-infra bug that  surfaced on the first attempt to drive this kernel through the standard test helpers.                                                                                                                  \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \r\n  **Motivation:** Gemma4 MoE blocks use gated GELU. Without this change, vLLM falls through to `Marlin` kernel when running quantized Gemma4 on Blackwell. Builds on #39510, whose non-aligned `intermediate_size` weight   padding is exercised by the new test at Gemma4's `(64, 704, 4096)` shape.                                                                                                                                                                                                                       \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  ## Changes                                                                                                                                                                                 \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  | File | Change |                                                                                                                                                                          \r\n  |---|---|                                                                                                                                                                                  \r\n  | `vllm/model_executor/layers/fused_moe/experts/trtllm_nvfp4_moe.py` | Add `MoEActivation.GELU` to `_supports_activation` and to the modular/monolithic `apply()` allow-list assertions. | \r\n  | `tests/kernels/moe/utils.py` | Add an `is_nvfp4_scale_swizzled` parameter (default `True`, preserves existing callers) to `make_test_quant_config`, forwarded to FusedMoEQuantConfig.make`. |                                                                                                                                                              \r\n  | `tests/kernels/moe/test_trtllm_nvfp4_moe.py` | **New file.** Kernel test exercising SiLU, RELU², and GELU at three shapes including Gemma4's `(intermediate_size=704, hidden=4096)`. |                                                                                                \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  The test-helper change is needed because the FlashInfer TRT-LLM kernel rejects swizzled (padded) input quant scales — its `numel`-based vec_size  derivation requires `numel == M*K/16`. Production code already does the  right thing in `oracle/nvfp4.py:458`; the test helper hardcoded the swizzled default, leaving the kernel untestable through `make_test_quant_config`.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  ## Test plan                                                                                                                                                                               \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  Ran on a Blackwell (SM100) box with FlashInfer-python 0.6.8.post1 and  flashinfer-cubin 0.6.8.post1.                                                                                                                       \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \r\n`  python -m pytest -v tests/kernels/moe/test_trtllm_nvfp4_moe.py --timeout=1200  `                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \r\n  **Result: 8 passed, 1 skipped, 0 failed.** All three GELU rows pass, including Gemma4's `(64, 704, 4096)`.                                                                                                                                             \r\n                                                                                                                                 \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n  The skip is `RELU2_NO_MUL @ (64, 704, 4096)` — FlashInfer's   `trtllm_batched_gemm_runner` raises *\"No valid config found for the given  problem shape\"* for non-gated RELU² at non-256-aligned `intermediate_size`.                                                                                                                              \r\n Verified pre-existing on `main` without this PR's changes; Does not affect Gemma4 enablement (Gemma4 uses gated GELU, not non-gated RELU²).  will raise an issue in Flashinfer, but not blocking this PR.                                                                                                             \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \r\n  The monolithic path (`TrtLlmNvFp4ExpertsMonolithic`) is gated identically  to the modular path. End-to-end coverage in this PR is on the modular path  (which is what Gemma4's multi-GPU expert-parallel deployments use). The  monolithic path was verified by probing `flashinfer.fused_moe.trtllm_fp4_block_scale_moe` directly with  `activation_type=Geglu`; the kernel accepts the call. Both entry points  share the same FlashInfer kernel family for the underlying compute.   \r\n<img width=\"2878\" height=\"1180\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8cc2d06f-0088-497c-bd17-2a1942057260\" />\r\n\r\n## Note-\r\n  - No production code changes for the swizzle issue. The oracle already sets the right flag in production.                                                                                  \r\n  - No GPU code changes — the kernel always supported GeGLU.\r\n  - No new dependencies, no FlashInfer version bump, no new dispatch paths.                                                                                                                  \r\n  - The monolithic path is gated identically to the modular path. The new test exercises the modular path end-to-end (the path Gemma4's expected multi-GPU-EP deployments use).\r\n\r\nAlso, when can the PR be picked in vllm latest image along with PR: https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/39510\r\n\r\n\r\n## TL;DR                                                                                                                                                       \r\n                  \r\nvLLM's Python allow-list rejected gated GELU on the TRT-LLM NvFP4 MoE backend, even though the underlying FlashInfer kernel supports it. This PR extends the allow-list to include MoEActivation.GELU (3 lines trtllm_nvfp4_moe.py). It also adds the first kernel-level test for TRT-LLM × NvFP4, which surfaced and fixes a latent test-helper bug around NvFP4 scale layout. ",
